('contractbook',
 'Contractbook',
 'Automate your entire contract workflow from creation to renewal in one platform',
 'Contractbook is a contract lifecycle management platform designed to bring all business contracts into a single, structured, searchable system. The core premise is that most companies manage contracts in a chaotic mix of email threads, shared folders, and physical files, making it impossible to track what has been agreed, when renewals are due, or what obligations exist across the business. Contractbook replaces that with a structured repository where every contract is stored with metadata, linked to the counterparty and deal, and searchable by term, value, or date. The AI layer assists with contract creation - generating first drafts from templates and briefs, suggesting standard clauses, and flagging unusual terms that deviate from the company standard. Automated workflows route contracts through the required approval steps before sending for signature, and renewal notifications alert responsible owners before contracts auto-renew or expire. Contractbook integrates with accounting systems, CRM tools, and HR platforms to pull relevant data into contracts automatically. The data extraction feature reads existing contracts and pulls key terms - start dates, values, renewal clauses, termination rights - into the database, making it practical to onboard a backlog of historical contracts. The platform is particularly useful for operations and legal teams at growing companies that have outgrown ad hoc contract management but are not ready for enterprise contract lifecycle management software. Pricing starts from $99 per month for small teams.',
 NULL,
 'https://contractbook.com',
 'https://contractbook.com',
