('ironclad',
 'Ironclad',
 'Enterprise digital contracting platform for legal teams managing complex contract workflows',
 'Ironclad is an enterprise digital contracting platform used by legal teams at companies including Dropbox, Mastercard, and L''Oreal to manage high-volume, complex contract workflows at scale. The platform is built around a visual workflow designer that lets legal and operations teams map out the complete lifecycle of a contract type, from request through negotiation, approval, signature, and archiving, with branching logic for different scenarios, jurisdictions, and counterparty types. Non-legal teams initiate contract requests through a guided intake form, answer questions about the deal, and the system generates a first draft, routes it for review, and tracks its progress through the defined workflow automatically. Ironclad AI assists with contract review by flagging deviations from standard playbook positions, suggesting alternative language, and summarising long contracts for business stakeholders who need to understand the key terms without reading the full document. The contract repository provides a searchable, filterable view of all contracts with extracted terms, obligation dates, and counterparty information. Ironclad positions itself as the operating system for legal teams, not just a storage and signature tool, but a workflow management system for the full contractual relationship between a company and its counterparties. The platform handles the full range of contract types - sales agreements, procurement contracts, NDAs, employment agreements, and partnership deals - within a single governance framework. Enterprise pricing is custom.',
 NULL,
